       ----ttrraacceeEExxcceeppttiioonnss
              For internal diagnostic use only.

       ----ppiiddffiilleeppaatthh <<ppaatthh>>
              Specifies  a  file location to store the process ID (PID) of the
              mmoonnggoodd process . The user  running  the  the  mmoonnggoodd  or  mmoonnggooss
              process must be able to write to this path. If the _-_-_p_i_d_f_i_l_e_p_a_t_h
              option is not specified, the process does not create a PID file.
              This option is generally only useful in combination with the the
              _-_-_f_o_r_k option.

                 Linux

                        On Linux, PID file management is generally the respon‐
                        sibility  of your distro's init system: usually a ser‐
                        vice file in the //eettcc//iinniitt..dd directory, or  a  systemd
                        unit  file  registered  with  ssyysstteemmccttll.  Only use the
                        _-_-_p_i_d_f_i_l_e_p_a_t_h option if you are not using one of these
                        init  systems.  For  more  information, please see the
                        respective Installation Guide for your operating  sys‐
                        tem.

                 macOS

                        On  macOS, PID file management is generally handled by
                        bbrreeww. Only use the _-_-_p_i_d_f_i_l_e_p_a_t_h option if you are not
                        using  bbrreeww  on  your macOS system.  For more informa‐
                        tion, please see the respective Installation Guide for
                        your operating system.

       ----kkeeyyFFiillee <<ffiillee>>
              Specifies  the  path to a key file that stores the shared secret
              that MongoDB instances use to authenticate to each  other  in  a
              sharded  cluster  or  replica set. _-_-_k_e_y_F_i_l_e implies _-_-_a_u_t_h. See
              inter-process-auth for more information.

