                 Windows  MongoDB deployments can use _-_-_l_d_a_p_B_i_n_d_W_i_t_h_O_S_D_e_f_a_u_l_t_s
                 instead of _-_-_l_d_a_p_Q_u_e_r_y_P_a_s_s_w_o_r_d and  _-_-_l_d_a_p_Q_u_e_r_y_P_a_s_s_w_o_r_d.  You
                 cannot      specify      both     _-_-_l_d_a_p_Q_u_e_r_y_P_a_s_s_w_o_r_d     and
                 _-_-_l_d_a_p_B_i_n_d_W_i_t_h_O_S_D_e_f_a_u_l_t_s at the same time.

       ----llddaappBBiinnddWWiitthhOOSSDDeeffaauullttss <<bbooooll>>
              _D_e_f_a_u_l_t: False

              New in version 3.4: Available in MongoDB Enterprise for the Win‐
              dows platform only.

              Allows mmoonnggoodd to authenticate, or bind, using your Windows login
              credentials when connecting to the LDAP server.

              Only required if:

              · Using LDAP authorization.

              · Using an LDAP query for _u_s_e_r_n_a_m_e _t_r_a_n_s_f_o_r_m_a_t_i_o_n.

