       ----rreeppaaiirr
              Changed in version 4.0.3.

              Runs  a  repair  routine on all databases for a _m_o_n_g_o_d instance.
              The operation attempts  to  salvage  corrupt  data  as  well  as
              rebuilds  all  the  indexes.  The operation discards any corrupt
              data that cannot be salvaged.

   TTiipp
       If you are running with journaling enabled, there is almost  never  any
       need  to  run  repair  since  the  server  can use the journal files to
       restore the data files to a clean state  automatically.   However,  you
       may  need  to  run  repair  in  cases  where you need to recover from a
       disk-level data corruption.

              WWAARRNNIINNGG::

                 · Before using _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r, make a backup  copy  of  the  _d_b_p_a_t_h
                   directory.

                 · Avoid running _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r against a replica set:

                   · To  repair  a  replica  set member, if you have an intact
                     copy of your data available (e.g. a recent backup  or  an
                     intact  member  of  the  replica  set), restore from that
                     intact copy instead(see /tutorial/resync-replica-set-mem‐
                     ber).

                   · If you do choose to run _m_o_n_g_o_d _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r against a replica
                     set member and the operation modifies  the  data  or  the
                     metadata,  you  must still perform a full resync in order
                     for the member to rejoin the replica set.

                 · Only  use  _m_o_n_g_o_d  _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r  (and  the  related  operations
                   rreeppaaiirrDDaattaabbaassee  command  and ddbb..rreeppaaiirrDDaattaabbaassee(()) method) if
                   you have no other options. The operations remove and do not
                   save any corrupt data during the repair process.

                 · If  repair  fails  to  complete  for  any  reason, you must
                   restart the instance using the _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r option.

              For MMAPv1 storage engine, see also _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r_p_a_t_h.

       ----rreeppaaiirrppaatthh <<ppaatthh>>
              _D_e_f_a_u_l_t: A __ttmmpp__rreeppaaiirrDDaattaabbaassee__<<nnuumm>> directory under the ddbbPPaatthh.

              _O_n_l_y _a_v_a_i_l_a_b_l_e _f_o_r _t_h_e _M_M_A_P_v_1 _s_t_o_r_a_g_e _e_n_g_i_n_e_.

              Specifies a working directory that MongoDB will use  during  the
              _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r  operation.  When  ----rreeppaaiirr completes, the _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r_p_a_t_h
              directory is empty, and ddbbPPaatthh contains the repaired files.

              The _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r_p_a_t_h must be within the ddbbPPaatthh. You  can  specify  a
              symlink  to  _-_-_r_e_p_a_i_r_p_a_t_h to use a path on a different file sys‐
              tem.

       ----jjoouurrnnaall
              Enables the durability journal to ensure data files remain valid
              and  recoverable.  This option applies only when you specify the
              _-_-_d_b_p_a_t_h option. mmoonnggoodd enables journaling by default.

              Not available for _m_o_n_g_o_d instances that use the in-memory  stor‐
              age engine.

              If any voting member of a replica set uses the in-memory storage
              engine,  you  must  set  wwrriitteeCCoonncceerrnnMMaajjoorriittyyJJoouurrnnaallDDeeffaauulltt   to
              ffaallssee.

              Starting in version 4.0.13 (and 3.6.14), if a replica set member
              uses the in-memory storage engine (voting or non-voting) but the
              replica  set has wwrriitteeCCoonncceerrnnMMaajjoorriittyyJJoouurrnnaallDDeeffaauulltt set to true,
              the replica set member logs a startup warning.

       ----nnoojjoouurrnnaall
              Disables journaling. mmoonnggoodd enables journaling by default.

              Not available for _m_o_n_g_o_d instances that use the in-memory  stor‐
              age engine.

              Starting  in  MongoDB 4.0, you cannot specify _-_-_n_o_j_o_u_r_n_a_l option
              or ssttoorraaggee..jjoouurrnnaall..eennaabblleedd:: ffaallssee for replica set  members  that
              use the WiredTiger storage engine.

       ----jjoouurrnnaallOOppttiioonnss <<aarrgguummeennttss>>
              _O_n_l_y _a_v_a_i_l_a_b_l_e _f_o_r _t_h_e _M_M_A_P_v_1 _s_t_o_r_a_g_e _e_n_g_i_n_e_.

              Provides  functionality  for  testing.  Not for general use, and
              will affect data file integrity in the case of  abnormal  system
              shutdown.

              Not  available for _m_o_n_g_o_d instances that use the in-memory stor‐
