       ----eennaabblleeMMaajjoorriittyyRReeaaddCCoonncceerrnn
              _D_e_f_a_u_l_t: True

              Starting  in MongoDB 3.6, MongoDB enables support for ""mmaajjoorriittyy""
              read concern by default.

              For MongoDB 4.0.3+ and 3.6.1+,  you  can  disable  read  concern
              ""mmaajjoorriittyy"" to prevent the storage cache pressure from immobiliz‐
              ing a deployment with a  three-member  primary-secondary-arbiter
              (PSA)  architecture.  For  more information about disabling read
              concern ""mmaajjoorriittyy"", see 4.0-disable-read-concern-majority.

              To disable, set _-_-_e_n_a_b_l_e_M_a_j_o_r_i_t_y_R_e_a_d_C_o_n_c_e_r_n to false.

              IIMMPPOORRTTAANNTT::
                 In general, avoid disabling ""mmaajjoorriittyy""  read  concern  unless
                 necessary.  However,  if  you have a three-member replica set
                 with a  primary-secondary-arbiter  (PSA)  architecture  or  a
                 sharded  cluster  with  a three-member PSA shards, disable to
                 prevent the storage  cache  pressure  from  immobilizing  the
                 deployment.

                 Disabling   ""mmaajjoorriittyy""  read  concern  disables  support  for
                 /changeStreams.

                 Disabling ""mmaajjoorriittyy"" does not affect multi-document  transac‐
                 tions;  i.e.  you  can  specify  read  concern "majority" for
                 multi-document transactions even if read  concern  "majority"
                 is disabled.

              _-_-_e_n_a_b_l_e_M_a_j_o_r_i_t_y_R_e_a_d_C_o_n_c_e_r_n  has no effect for MongoDB versions:
              4.0.0, 4.0.1, 4.0.2, 3.6.0.

   SShhaarrddeedd CClluusstteerr OOppttiioonnss
       ----ccoonnffiiggssvvrr
              _R_e_q_u_i_r_e_d _i_f _s_t_a_r_t_i_n_g _a _c_o_n_f_i_g _s_e_r_v_e_r_.

              Declares that this mmoonnggoodd instance serves as the  config  server
              of  a  sharded  cluster.  When running with this option, clients
              (i.e. other cluster components) cannot write data to  any  data‐
